<span id="freeTextContainer4013689297398721885">In this comedy, Machiavelli teaches how to be a good con artist. He shows how bad guys can win over good guys because they are liars and good guys will believe them. A man joins forces with a con man to fool a good guy telling him that his wife would conceive a boy heir if she eats the mandragola leaves, but the man who sleeps with her for the first time after she eats the leaves would die, so the husband has to allow someone else to sleep with her. The husband being a good guy believes this con</span>
  <span id="freeText4013689297398721885" style="display:none">In this comedy, Machiavelli teaches how to be a good con artist. He shows how bad guys can win over good guys because they are liars and good guys will believe them. A man joins forces with a con man to fool a good guy telling him that his wife would conceive a boy heir if she eats the mandragola leaves, but the man who sleeps with her for the first time after she eats the leaves would die, so the husband has to allow someone else to sleep with her. The husband being a good guy believes this con man and allows him to sleep with his wife. The wife is evil as well, so the two of them end up making a fool out of the husband. It is funny but very sad.</span>
