        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2131479574" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4494961914428685651">4.5/5<br/>*Read for class. <br/><br/>Surprisingly for me, this was amazing! I loved almost every word of it, the comedy element was great and the story itself was quite interesting. So, so glad I&apos;ve read this. <br/><br/>I&apos;m only taking 0.5 star off because of some sexism (I mean, I know it&apos;s 16th century, but still) and for the philosophy &quot;the end justifies the means&quot;. <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[I get it, her husband was rather stupid. But he seemed loving and wanting a baby so much? Just very naive. Don&apos;t know, conflicted about hi</span></span>
  <span id="freeText4494961914428685651" style="display:none">4.5/5<br />*Read for class. <br /><br />Surprisingly for me, this was amazing! I loved almost every word of it, the comedy element was great and the story itself was quite interesting. So, so glad I've read this. <br /><br />I'm only taking 0.5 star off because of some sexism (I mean, I know it's 16th century, but still) and for the philosophy "the end justifies the means". <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I get it, her husband was rather stupid. But he seemed loving and wanting a baby so much? Just very naive. Don't know, conflicted about him being deceived by out main character. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span></span>
  <a data-text-id="4494961914428685651" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

